Loading president result

president_vote <- readxl::read_xlsx('twdata/president.xlsx') %>% 
  mutate(total = chu + tsai + song) %>% 
  mutate(chu_ratio = chu / total,
         tsai_ratio = tsai / total,
         song_ratio = song / total,
         tsai_chu_ratio = tsai / chu)

Join presendental data to shp

### install.packages("gpclib")
# unproj <- CRS("+proj=longlat +datum=WGS84")
# library(maptools);library(gpclib)
county_shp_df <- broom::tidy(county_shp, region = 'COUNTYNAME') %>%
  left_join(president_vote, by = c('id' = 'county'))

Draw county level map

# install.packages("mapproj")
county_shp_df %>% 
  ggplot() + 
    geom_polygon(aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group,fill = tsai_chu_ratio), colour = 'gray')+
    scale_fill_gradient2(high = "#a3e2c5", low = "#2200ff", midpoint = 1) +
    ggplot2::coord_map(xlim = c(119, 122.5), ylim = c(21.8, 25.5)) +
    theme_void()

Town level

Read town level data

town_shp <- readOGR('shapefiles/', layer = "town", encoding = 'utf-8', stringsAsFactors = F)
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "/Users/jirlong/Dropbox/Programming/R/R4CSS/05_viz/shapefiles", layer: "town"
## with 368 features
## It has 7 fields
town_shp@data <- town_shp@data %>% 
  mutate(TOWNNAME = iconv(TOWNNAME, "utf-8"), 
         COUNTYNAME = iconv(COUNTYNAME, "utf-8"))

Load only Taipei data

taipei_income <- readxl::read_xlsx('twdata/台北各區每人所得.xlsx') 
taipei_town <- town_shp@data %>% filter(COUNTYNAME == "臺北市")

Join data with shp

town_shp_df <- broom::tidy(town_shp, region = 'TOWNNAME') %>% 
  filter(id %in% taipei_town$TOWNNAME) %>% 
  left_join(taipei_income, by = c("id" = "district"))
